sub_title: Kolonel special assignment to the FARDC. with Expertise in Strategic & Military Operations Experience in Conflict Resolution & Diplomacy.
summary:
Nguba Bolikango is the grandson of Nguba Honore from 4th Commando Battalion Province de Province de la Mongala & Jean Akpolokaka Gbukulu Nzete Nzube Bolikango whom is the "fathers of independence" in the Congo.

He has served for 20 years in the royal dutch army, with five deployment to Kosovo, Bosnia, Iraq and twice to Afghanistan. 
After finding out his family’s history, Nguba now wants to again follow in his grandfather Jean Bolikango’s footsteps as a ‘Father of Independence’ in the Congo and grandfather’s Nguba Honore to support in rebuilding United Congo.

He transferred from Royal Netherlands Army to Armed Forces of the Democratic Republic of the Congo and now fights for the Congolees people, with as his guideline the Manifeste de Conscience Africaine, in and out of the country with the same daring and tenacity that made him a top gun in the Royal Netherlands Army.
